============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Prime Number Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      π(n) ~ n/ln(n)
Applications: Cryptography, algorithm analysis
Discoverer:   Hadamard/de la VP (1896)

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

Theorem/Law:  Binomial Theorem
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      (a+b)^n = sum of C(n,k) a^k b^(n-k)
Applications: Probability, statistics, polynomial algebra
Discoverer:   Newton/Pascal (1665)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Dialectical Materialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   History driven by material economic forces through thesis-antithesis-synthesis
Philosopher:  Karl Marx/Hegel
Example:      Class struggle between bourgeoisie and proletariat drives history

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

